Minister of Youth and Sports Development Sunday Dare over the weekend organised table tennis competition in honour of late Oba Jimoh Oyewumi, the Soun of Ogbomoso. According to the Minister, the maiden DAD Foundation Table Tennis Competition was part of activities lined up for the 40 days Fidau prayers in honour of the late monarch. It would be recalled that Oba Oyewumi died on December 12 at the age of 95. The Minister noted that the competition was to promote peace and engaged the youths to make them productive and annex their talents.   Burkina Faso 1-1 Gabon (7-6 pens): Ouedraogo hits winning…     Joshua hell bent to reclaim belt from Usyk     Sportsville Award holds Feb 13   He however urged the youth not to limit themselves and be committed, saying that there is great opportunity in sport. - Advertisement - Meanwhile, the former Director, Kwara State Sports Council Tunde Kazeem while speaking at the event described the Minister as an exemplary performer whose accessibility and humility is unparalleled for leaders of his kind. The President, Ogbomoso Community Youth Forum, Rev. Peter Olaleye commended Dare for not only initiating the competition but for investing in the on-going construction of a befitting Sports centre for the town. Representative of the Minister’s friends, Dr. Dan Okeke, an APC chieftain from Abia State, stated that they are in Ogbomoso to support the Minister because he was always there for his friends despite his hectic schedule. Cash gifts were later presented to the winners of competition by the Minister as the community looks forward to the commissioning of the Sports centre in a few weeks.